included.summary: I am the User Experience Researcher for American Greetings, and previously served as the User Experience Researcher and as a User Experience Designer for Finastra. I graduated with my Master of Arts in Professional Communication from Clemson University in May 2016. My diverse background includes usability, public relations, social media, copywriting, and marketing.
included.headline: User Experience Researcher at American Greetings

included.description: I created this photo montage as part of my graduate visual communications course at Clemson University. I have passed this old Christian school several times. Each time I drive by the building, I find myself wondering what it was like when it was brimming with people and the stories it would be able to tell. I have always been interested in abandoned buildings, and I thought this school building would present a fantastic narrative. Figuring it would be perfect for a photo montage, I decided on the theme of abandonment. Through images and haikus, I hope I have done justice to this building and the sadness and beauty in its abandonment. Copyright 2015, Danielle Shuff
included.title: Abandonment: Seeing Beauty in the Broken
